modules.description: Creates a window object with metadata, allowing checks for whether the window is full. Operates on a parameterized type representing window states. Used to manage buffer limits in real-time data processing pipelines.

Handles reading and writing of Git PACK files, including decompression and object extraction. Works with binary data structures representing Git objects such as commits, trees, blobs, and tags. Used to efficiently retrieve individual objects from a compressed pack without decompressing the entire file.

Manages real-time data processing windows with state-aware operations, tracking buffer limits through a parameterized type. Provides checks for window fullness and supports dynamic state transitions. Operations include window creation, state inspection, and buffer management. Examples include monitoring incoming data streams and enforcing rate limits based on window capacity.
